<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step09_WhenAny"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      Title="Step 9 - Task.WhenAny">
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 9: Task.WhenAny - Responding to the First Result"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">WHEN ANY: React as soon as the FIRST task completes.

Task.WhenAll waits for ALL tasks. Task.WhenAny waits for just the FIRST one.

Use cases:
- Race condition: Query 3 servers, use whichever responds first.
- Timeout: Start your operation AND a delay. If the delay finishes first,
  your operation took too long.
- Processing as available: Start many downloads, process each as it completes.

Task.WhenAny returns the Task that finished first. You can inspect it to see
which task "won the race."</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="Race: Which server responds first?"
                    Click="Race_Click"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="Timeout pattern: Operation with 2-second timeout"
                    Click="Timeout_Click"/>

            <TextBox x:Name="Output" Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
